					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>There's two kinds of smokers:</p><p>A) The smoker who refuses to expose anyone else to their second-hand smoke. These smokers should be left alone to smoke themselves silly if they so wish. They certainly shouldn't have to apply for a bloody smoking licence. </p><p>And then there's:</p><p>B) The smoker who doesn't give a flying f**k if you're exposed to their second hand smoke, regardless of its affect on your lungs, asthma or clothes and who screams `p**s off somewhere else then!` when you even politely try and point out that if you don't fart repeatedly in their face, the least they can do is not waft foul toxic fumes into yours.</p><p>The smokers in category B, unlike the decent considerate smokers in category A, deserve no sympathy whatsoever.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
