					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>The idea of making a permit deliberately difficult to obtain is stupid for any number of reasons.  However, having a permit is a wonderful idea.  Smokers light up wherever the alfred they want, smoke in front of children, blow smoke in other people's faces, and generally display a lack of understand of the rules they ought to be observing.</p><p>Just like a driving theory test, there ought to be a small theory test for a smoker's permit.  Anyone who fails to get 'smoke outdoors, ensure a safe distance from people who have to pass by, and dispose of the cigarette butts in a garbage can' right should be failed, and, naturally, made to pay forty quid for a new appointment.  It's only fair.</p><p></p>
						
