                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I work with ex-offenders. Most of them smoke; they have enough problems in their lives without giving up tobacco as well. They, like many others, wouldn't apply for a permit. We have much tobacco smuggling already and permits would be a major boost to it and many ordinary smokers would get their first exposure to their friendly, neighbourhood dealer who may also have a choice of heroin, crack and other nasties.
LeGrand actually acknowledged the contraband problem, but if he's serious, he can have no real idea of the extent of this problem. Permits would be a gift to organised crime and stuff more people into our overcrowded prisons which would even less manageable thanks to the threats, bullying and violence as the inmates fight for their tobacco. 
Thanks Charlie
</p>
						
					</div>
