					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>For those with delicate lungs or who work in dusty/noxious environments there are devices which look a bit like transparent welder's masks. They have a battery powered device bottom front that filters the air, thus protecting the lungs. Versions fitted with ear defenders/headphones are also available.</p><p>I propose that anyone wishing to smoke should do so whilst wearing a modified device, one that filters the air inside so that all air exiting is clean. Since we are told by them that tobacco smoke is not only harmless but also pleasant this should enhance the smoking pleasure as it will raise the level of smoke around the head of the smoker.</p><p>I further propose that the air intake be sited at the back of the device and shaped so that it is easily obstructed by say a hand or crumpled paper so that the rest of us can have a laugh. To prevent cheating it will be necessary to have air quality sensors around the outside of the helmet, any deviation from air quality standards will result in the miscreant being injected in the neck with cyanide (at a higher does than they are getting anyway). </p><p>Don't stand too near busy roads now...</p><p></p>
						
