					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Brave New World.
Soon smokers will be forced to switch to soma. Instead of giving our money to the now disgraced tobacco companies, we will have to turn to the Pharma industry to get our nicotine kick. I don't think it's an improvement.</p><p>I don't understand why people have suddenly become so paranoid about the risk of smoking (or passive smoking). We have been smoking tobacco for thousands of years in some parts of the planet and for at least 500 years in Europe. </p><p>How bad can a plant be for us, considering the amount of chemicals we have to put up with everyday (and not out of choice)? I don't drive, cycle to work,  run marathons, swim, eat a healthy vegetarian diet, don't have a tv, and hate disposable products. I even carry a flask everyday to avoid buying water, coffee, and tea in disposable bottles and cups. </p><p>I also love my ciggies. They help me relax, and concentrate (for which many people now take pills!) 
I wonder why i have to be treated like a criminal, and be profiled, for doing what people have been happily doing for generations. </p><p>How many people who complain about second-hand smoke actually drive, buy useless consumer products, waste energy, take planes, and directly or indirectly pollute the air i breathe every day?
Before they get on their high-horse and condemn smokers they should take a look at their lifestyle first. </p><p>If they are so concerned about lung cancer, they should tell me why in the Swiss Alps where people smoke a lot the rates of lung cancer are so low. Has it ever occured to them that you have to take into account many more causes than just smoking to explain cancer?</p><p>And if somebody asks me whether i prefer to die a few years earlier, as a happy smoker or turn into a 90 y/o vegetable in a wheelchair, spoonfed by nurses, i would opt for the first. We live in  an overpopulated planet that cannot sustain our wasteful lifestyles...why do we care so much if its population dies a bit earlier than expected? If tobacco doesn't kill us, war will, or maybe climate change, or stress, or any of the other cancers. 
Smoking is a pleasure you choose as an adult, on the other hand breathing exhaust fumes, eating pesticides, or handling cancerogenic substances in a factory is a lot less fun...but nobody gives you the choice to say no.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
				<li class="comment-tools">
					<ul>
						<li class="recomended">
							
